#!/usr/bin/env python3
"""
tuxpatch - RHEL workstation patch manager with TPM2/LUKS reseal support

TPM2/LUKS reseal strategy (clevis, two-boot):
  Pre-update  : Switch all clevis bindings from PCR-protected to TPM-only
                (no PCR restrictions).  The disk will still unlock on the
                next boot via the TPM — no password needed.
  Post-update : A one-shot systemd service runs early in the *next* boot,
                rebinds clevis against the fresh PCR measurements produced
                by the new shim/kernel, then reboots one final time so the
                system boots normally with full PCR protection restored.
"""

